1. d4 d5 2. c4 e5 { Albin counter-gambit } 3. dxe5 d4 4. e3 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 dxe3 6. fxe3 { fxe3 is best move for white here. } (6. Qa4+ Nc6 7. Bxb4 exf2+ 8. Kxf2 Qh4+ 9. g3 Qd4+ { one R will fall } 10. Kg2 (10. Ke2 Qxb2+ 11. Nd2 Qxa1) (10. Ke1 Qe4+ 11. Kf2 Qxh1) (10. Kf3 Bg4+ 11. Kg2 Qe4+ 12. Kf2 Qxh1) 10... Qxb2+ 11. Be2 Qxa1) (6. Bxb4 exf2+ 7. Ke2 (7. Kxf2 Qxd1) 7... fxg1=N+ 8. Rxg1 (8. Ke1 Qh4+ 9. g3 (9. Kd2 Nc6 { [%cal Gc6b4,Gc8g4,Gg4d1,Ge8c8,Ga8d8,Gd8d2] }) 9... Qe4+ { capture R }) 8... Bg4+) 6... Qh4+ 7. g3 Qe4 { Q attacking R, e5 and e3 (white B pinned) } *

