{ 5 Queen's Gambit Traps Every Chess Player Should Know - by Eric Rosen
https://lichess.org/video/6r_VKSdpRH8
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6r_VKSdpRH8 }
1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 { Slav defense } 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Nf3 Bf5 { This position could be arrived at through different move orders.
When playing as black against queens gambit, need to be careful of developing light square B early because Qb3 can be threatening. } 5. cxd5 cxd5 6. Qb3 { [%cal Gb3b7,Gb3d5] } 6... Qb6 (6... Bc8 { best move for black }) (6... b6 7. Bg5 { Eric's move } (7. e4 { top engine move }) 7... e6 8. e4 dxe4 9. Bb5+ Nbd7 10. Ne5 Be7 11. Bxf6 gxf6 12. Nxd7) 7. Nxd5 { white is up a p. } 7... Qxb3 8. Nxf6+ exf6 9. axb3 { white is up a p and has two centre p's vs 0 centre p's } *
